Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @lamb steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into 1cm chunks.

Trim and halve the @green beans{80%grams}.

== Tzatziki ==

Trim the @baby cucumber{1}, then halve lengthways. Cut lengthways into roughly 1cm wide strips, then cut into 1cm pieces widthways.

Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams}, cucumber, mint, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, a squeeze of lemon juice and pinch of lemon zest. Season with @salt{}. Set your tzatziki aside.

== Lamb ==

Season the steaks with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the pan is hot, carefully lay in the lamb steaks.

Fry until golden, ~{2%minutes} each side, then transfer to a medium baking tray.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven for ~{5%minutes} for medium-rare.

> Cook for a few more mins if you prefer yours more well done. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The lamb is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

Once cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

== Charred Greens ==

Meanwhile, wipe out the (now empty) pan and pop back on high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the courgette and green beans. Cook until tender and charred, ~{7-9%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add a squeeze of lemon juice and cook until evaporated.

Crumble in half the @Greek style salad cheese{100%grams} and toss to coat the veg, then set aside and cover to keep warm.

== To Serve ==

When you're ready to serve, slice the lamb steaks widthways into 1cm thick slices, then share between your #plates{}.

Serve the roasted potatoes and charred veg alongside, then crumble over the remaining Greek style salad cheese. Scatter with the @toasted flaked almonds{15%grams}.

Finish with a dollop of tzatziki and serve any remaining lemon wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!